Four years ago, a 45-year-old Indian painter lost both of his hands in a tr=
ain accident.=20
That=E2=80=99s a devastating accident for anyone, let alone a painter from =
an underprivileged background. And until recently, it would have been perma=
nent.=20
But this week, a team of doctors at Sir Ganga Ram Hospital completed the fi=
rst successful bilateral hand transplant in Delhi=E2=80=99s history.=20
=E2=80=9CThe surgery, which took more than 12 hours, involved connecting ev=
ery artery, muscle, tendon and nerve between the donor's [Meena Mehta] hand=
s and the recipient's arms.=E2=80=9D=20
I mean, that=E2=80=99s just an unbelievable W for the painter, and for huma=
nity.=20
Give those doctors a hand!=20
